  "prompt": "Can we know if our card has been inserted in ATM?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several ways to know if your card has been inserted in an ATM:\n\n1. Physical indicators:\n- The card slot will typically illuminate or show a blinking light\n- The screen will usually display a prompt or message indicating card detection\n- Many modern ATMs have a card insertion confirmation screen\n\n2. Sensory cues:\n- You'll hear a mechanical sound when the card is pulled inside the machine\n- The machine will briefly hold/grip the card during the initial insertion\n\n3. Screen messages:\n- \"Card detected\"\n- \"Please wait\"\n- \"Processing your transaction\"\n- Specific prompts related to your bank or card type\n\n4. Card retention:\n- If the machine retains your card for processing, it's definitely inserted\n- Some ATMs partially extend the card out after reading\n\n5. Safety tips:\n- Always watch the card insertion process carefully\n- If the card feels stuck or doesn't move smoothly, cancel the transaction\n- Check for any suspicious devices around the card slot\n\n6. Technology variations:\n- Different ATM models might have slightly different insertion mechanisms\n- Modern machines often have more sophisticated card detection systems\n\nRemember to stay alert and observant during ATM transactions to ensure your card's safety.",
